values: ... not much to say.  been awhile since i've written anything here.  things are still the same..  still at gamestop.. still broke.. and.. yet again, my friends seemed to have vanished.  i'm really getting sick of it.  they resurface for like a second..  pretend to actually care about my existance.. then disappear again.  i keep telling myself to forget about them.. it's not worth it.  but i can't help but think about how much fun i used to have..  ages ago...  oh well.. maybe it's for the better, anyway.  i just wish i wasn't so alone.  i have very few people in my life.. and while the ones i do have are incredibly important to me and all i need, really.. i just don't understand why people don't like me.  yes i'm shy..  yes i'm quiet..  but am i really that horrible to hang out with?   what is it about me that's so terrible??  hell.. if anyone can fill me in, that'd be great.  then again.. what difference does it really make..

I Am A: Neutral Good Elf Ranger Fighter

Alignment:
Neutral Good characters believe in the power of good above all else. They will work to make the world a better place, and will do whatever is necessary to bring that about, whether it goes for or against whatever is considered 'normal'.

Race:
Elves are the eldest of all races, although they are generally a bit smaller than humans. They are generally well-cultured, artistic, easy-going, and because of their long lives, unconcerned with day-to-day activities that other races frequently concern themselves with. Elves are, effectively, immortal, although they can be killed. After a thousand years or so, they simply pass on to the next plane of existance.

Primary Class:
Rangers are the defenders of nature and the elements. They are in tune with the Earth, and work to keep it safe and healthy.

Secondary Class:
Fighters are the warriors. They use weapons to accomplish their goals. This isn't to say that they aren't intelligent, but that they do, in fact, believe that violence is frequently the answer.

Deity:
Mielikki is the Neutral Good goddess of the forest and autumn. She is also known as the Lady of the Forest, and is the Patron of Rangers. Her followers are devoted to nature, and believe in the positive and outreaching elements of it. They use light armor, and a variety of weapons suitable for hunting, which they are quite skilled at. Mielikki's symbol is a unicorn head.

after much struggle, strength, and one hell of a fight death finally won the battle.  my uncle charlie passed away this evening.  i have mixed emotions about this... without getting into the story it might be hard for you guys to understand.. but i don't really want to talk about it.  of course i'm horribly sad.. but i'm also about as angry as they can come.. yet some part of me is at peace knowing that his pain is finally over.  it isn't fair..  but that's life, right?  

^*^

please keep my mom, aunt, family, and of course my uncle charlie in your thoughts...

well, the anime convention is now over  *sigh*  sad really.. but next year i think i might go all 3 days.. maybe even get a hotel room.  i think i'll have a different costume for each day as well.  so far i'm thinking i'll bring the Redmage costume for a comeback for friday, saturday will be a mithra in full RSE (final fantasy xi), and sunday i'll go as Morrigan (Dark Stalkers).  but who knows, the convention is a full year away.. i may change my mind.  but what i do know is i had a lot of fun this year, and my costume was an even bigger success than i thought it would be.  i'm trying to see if there's another convention in/near chicago this summer, if there is.. i'm totally going!  
*laughs*  yet another Sheep/Pigface show is coming up.  so of course.. i'll be there.  it's on sunday.. not exactly sure who's going to that yet.  and lastly, i'm still determined to make my way to london.  the idea of 2 rachels in england is just to inviting to ignore.  lol  who knows what kind of trouble we'll get ourselves into.  :p  alright, that's all for now.. i'm freezing so i think i'm gonna try to warm up.. and read for awhile.

i am seriously attempting to go to england for 5 days to a week some time in september.  i think i'm gonna go to a travel agency on tuesday to get some information about it.  so far i'm thinking.. clubbing and phantom of the opera (and of course the various Beatles locations).  unfortunately.. i don't know if it'll happen because my job pays close to nothing :(  but.. hey.. it doesn't hurt to look into it.  i bet shopping is pretty cool there too.. 

on another note.. i've decided that there are tons of video games i want.. but i'll never be able to afford!  one i'm definately getting though got traded in the other day, Darkstalkers 3 wee!  it's 14.99 though, so i have to wait awhile before picking it up.                                                                                                                                   most the other games i want are for the gamecube (i need more games for that system)  smash bros, paper mario, killer 7, and ailien hominid would all be most welcomed.  as far as the PS2 goes.. lego star wars and there's a game coming out called Haunting Grounds that seems fun.  i'll just leave that list there for anyone that's feeling generous to look over... *cough Mike cough*  (if you're reading this, mike... lego and paper come first!)  

let's see...  i really need to go out more, so i can actually have things to write about in this thing lol. the convention is now 2 weeks away!  the costume is coming along wonderfully.  i'm a little worried about the hat though.. lol  but i'm sure i'll figure something out.   ok.. i'm gonna stop writing before everyone falls asleep while reading.  lol.. i promise one day.. i'll have something important to say. 

                                                                   ^*^

The anime convention fast approaches (yup i fully plan to be one of those dorks) my costume is coming alone nicely.. if only i could shake off the lazy and get to work on it so i can finish it.  i'm going to work on the cloak tomorrow, should get it all done except for the extras.. ie the trim and clasps and such.  the next step is then the hat.. yikes!  never made a hat before.. first time for everything..   after that it'll be smooth sailing.  just hemming and lil extras, and we can't forget to make my plastic sword look metal.  

~Anyway~

i sent some more resumes and aps to the Field Museum.  gift shop and volunteer.... yea.. there's a good use of a bio degree..  oh well.  i'm thinking of maybe taking some photography classes.. be like a freelance nature photographer.  thought that might be fun.

i don't know about that emo shit..

well.. my birthday came and went.. didn't really do anything special.  but the day before it was a lot of fun.. saw some people i haven't seen in months.  

been a mess lately.  my marni died last tuesday.  for those of you that don't know, she is my dog and my best friend.  maybe that sounds silly to some of you.. but she was the one individual that was always there for me, no matter what.  she listened.. and i know she understood.  i came home from work or school or just from being with friends.. she'd greet me at the door.. tail wagging :)  i miss her..  and i can't seem to get used to the fact that she isn't here.  i expect her to be there when i leave my room.  i have to stop myself from tossing pizza crust on the floor (she loved the crust!!)  the list goes on.. and so do the tears and the hurt.  she's been with the family since i was 5..  i didn't even get to say goodbye.. she died while i was asleep..  i woke up the next morning at 6 to my mom in my room.. she only said my name.. but i knew what she was going to say..   i miss her....
